The paper deals with the problem of answering linear queries on a database, subject to differential privacy. This problem is closely related to data structures (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
